-- Update main course description with verbatim intro
UPDATE courses SET description = 'Overview
Introduction
In this program you will design and implement a fully functioning smartwatch by combining low
level driver development, embedded systems programming, and system-level integration.
You''ll work on the LilyGo T-Watch 2020 V3, a real commercial smartwatch platform, and write
production-style firmware entirely in C and C++: the same languages used in industry for
resource-constrained embedded systems
● C is used for low-level hardware control and communication
● C++ enables modular design, abstraction, and higher-level application logic
Throughout the program you''ll build your system incrementally using provided training materials,
reference implementations, and targeted code examples. These resources are designed to
support you without removing the need for engineering decision making.
If you need help, email support@shortcct.com with your specific questions and a zip file
including your project directory. Remember, virtual support is available for 3 months after your
product delivery date.'
