-- Add overview content including Recommended Background, Industry Alignment, Documentation, Setup
UPDATE lessons SET content_json = '{"sections": [{"title": "Recommended Background", "content": "Recommended Background\nThis projects is designed for students who want hands-on embedded firmware experience. You\ndo not need a lot of experience, but some foundational knowledge is expected.\nRequired\n\u25cf Introductory programming experience in C or C++\n\u25cf Comfort with basic programming concepts such as functions, control flow, arrays, and\nstructs\nHelpful\n\u25cf Introductory exposure to embedded systems\n\u25cf Introductory electronics knowledge\nIf you find that you are missing some of this background, reach out to us at\nsupport@shortcct.com and we can explore options to get you up to speed!\n\n=== PAGE 2 ==="}, {"title": "Industry Alignment", "content": "Industry Alignment\nWe analyzed the most in-demand skills across 50+ companies hiring embedded systems\nengineering interns. Below is how the Smartwatch Project aligns with those skills.\nCore skills are fully covered in the base project.\nExtendable skills can be developed through optional project extensions and the design\nchallenge.\nNot Covered indicates skills that are outside the scope of the core project."}, {"title": "Documentation", "content": "Documentation\nHere is the relevant documentation that you will need to use throughout the development of\nyour project:\n\n=== PAGE 3 ===\n\nDatasheets\nAXP202 Datasheet\nPCF8563 Datasheet\nST7789V Datasheet\nFT6236U Datasheet\nBMA423 Datasheet\nLibraries\nTFT_eSPI Library\nAXP202X_Library\nBMA423_Library\nOther\nT-Watch Pinout\nT-Watch Schematic"}, {"title": "Setup", "content": "Set Up Smartwatch\nTo set up Platform IO, this video by DroneBot Workshop is a great resource. It includes\ninstallation steps for Linux, MacOS, and Windows. You can download the latest versions of\nPython and Visual Studio Code\nOnce you have downloaded PlatformIO on your system, watch the following video to set up your\nenvironment for our project\nThe following video shows you how to clone our github repository,\nshort-circuit-projects/smartwatch, to VSCode. This tutorial is done on Windows, so it will look\ndifferent on Linux or MacOS.\nAdd the video labeled Smartwatch Setup Tutorial here\n\n=== PAGE 4 ==="}], "verbatim_source": "Smartwatch Project Full Documentation PDF"}'
WHERE id = 'lesson-t-overview';

